Passwd::Keyring::Memory

Passwd::Keyring is about using secure storage for passwords
and other credentials used in perl scripts and applications.

Passwd::Keyring::Memory is fallback module used by
Passwd::Keyring::Auto whenever no better keyring is
available. Passwords are preserved only temporarily, while the program
is running and not saved anywhere.

The module also illustrates Keyring backend API.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Keyring::MemoryOnly

You can also look for information at:

    http://bitbucket.org/Mekk/perl-keyring

